The best way to learn data structures is to implement them from memory.

Pseudocode


```
class SparseTable:
    function init(arr):
        this.n=arr.length
        this.LOG=array of size(this.n+1),filled with 0
        for i=2 to this.n:
            this.LOG[i]=this.LOG[i / 2]+1

        K=this.LOG[this.n]+1
        this.st=2D array of size this.n x K,filled with 0

        for i=0 to this.n - 1:
            this.st[i][0]=arr[i]

        for j=1 to K - 1:
            for i=0 to this.n -(1 << j):
                this.st[i][j]=min(this.st[i][j-1],this.st[i+(1 <<(j-1))][j-1])function query(l,r):
        k=this.LOG[r - l+1]
        return min(this.st[l][k],this.st[r -(1 << k)+1][k])
```

Preprocessing: O(nlogn). Each query: O(1).

